# Code Organization Rules

## Constants
- All constants MUST be defined in `lib/constants/` directory
- Constants should be exported with UPPER_SNAKE_CASE names
- Related constants should be grouped in the same file
- NO inline constants in components

## Types
- All types/interfaces MUST be defined in `lib/types/` directory
- Display types (for UI mapping) go in `lib/types/display.ts`
- Component props types can stay in component files if only used once
- Shared types MUST be in `lib/types/`
- NO inline type definitions in components unless they are component-specific props

## Utils
- All utility functions MUST be in `lib/utils/` directory
- Group related utilities in the same file (e.g., date utilities in `date.ts`)
- NO inline utility functions in components
- Reusable formatting, validation, and helper functions should be extracted

## Components
- Components should ONLY contain UI logic and state management
- NO constants, types, or utils defined inside components
- Use custom hooks for complex state management
- Keep components focused on rendering and user interaction

## File Structure
- Follow the existing directory structure
- Group related files together
- Use descriptive file names
